---
import BaseLayout from "../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
---

<BaseLayout title="Disclaimer" currentPath="/disclaimer/">
  <h1>Disclaimer</h1>
  <p class="lead">Please read before using this preview site or exported data files.</p>

  <div class="banner banner--review" role="alert">
    <strong>Not legal advice.</strong> Caesar AI Regulation Watch does not provide legal advice, regulatory
    opinions, or compliance guarantees.
  </div>

  <div class="prose">
    <h2>No compliance guarantee</h2>
    <p>
      This product helps teams <strong>identify</strong> tracked official sources and changes that may warrant
      internal governance review. It does <strong>not</strong> determine legal obligations, compliance status,
      or approval by any regulator or authority.
    </p>

    <h2>Not complete global coverage</h2>
    <p>
      The registry is incremental and pilot-scoped. Absence of a jurisdiction, law, or topic does not mean
      no regulation applies. Do not rely on this site as an exhaustive legal survey.
    </p>

    <h2>Sample and incomplete data</h2>
    <p>
      Many records are manual samples for data-model testing. Summaries, dates, and change detections may be
      incomplete, fictionalised, or outdated. <strong>Verify all material facts on official sources</strong>{" "}
      before client use.
    </p>

    <h2>Human review required</h2>
    <p>
      Content with <code>pending_review</code>, <code>draft</code>, or <code>manual_sample</code> origin must
      not be used in client deliverables without qualified professional review appropriate to your
      organisation and jurisdiction.
    </p>

    <h2>Official sources control</h2>
    <p>
      When this site and an official source disagree, <strong>the official source controls</strong>. Use the
      “View official source” links on record pages as the primary reference.
    </p>

    <h2>Export samples</h2>
    <p>
      JSON exports and RSS feeds are generated from the same pilot YAML. Export samples are{" "}
      <strong>not client evidence</strong> and do not create records in Caesar AI Evidence or Governance OS.
    </p>

    <h2>No warranty</h2>
    <p>
      This preview is provided as-is for product development and governance workflow design. Caesar and
      contributors disclaim warranties to the fullest extent permitted by law.
    </p>
  </div>

  <p><a href="/methodology/">Read methodology →</a></p>
</BaseLayout>
